{
  "texts": [
    "The causal ResNet model (PCC = 0.797) achieved a performance comparable to that of the non-causal model (PCC = 0.806), with no significant differences between the two (Wilcoxon two-sided signed-rank test P = 0.093).",
    "The same was true for the causal Swin model (PCC = 0.798) and its non-causal (PCC = 0.792) counterpart (Wilcoxon two-sided signed-rank test P = 0.196).",
    "In contrast, the performance of the causal LSTM model (PCC = 0.712) was significantly inferior to that of its non-causal (PCC = 0.745) version (Wilcoxon two-sided signed-rank test P = 0.009).",
    "Furthermore, the LSTM model showed consistently lower performance than ResNet and Swin.",
    "However, we did not find significant differences between the causal ResNet and causal Swin performances (Wilcoxon two-sided signed-rank test P = 0.587)."
  ]
}